title.@value: Incomplete uterine prolapse with anterior vaginal wall prolapse

definition.@value: A condition characterised by the displacement of the uterus from its normal position into the vaginal area in association with herniation of the bladder into the vagina due to tearing of the tough fibrous wall between a woman's bladder and her vagina (the pubovesical fascia).
